The paper discusses the modeling and analysis of power-consumption outage in wireless communication systems, specifically in millimeter wave (mmWave) massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) base stations (BSs) and smartphones. This involves both communication and heat transfer theories, indicating a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The analysis also considers the impact on the overall system performance, suggesting a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of mmWave massive MIMO technology implies a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and architecture (cs.AR).
